  intro: 'When customs violations occur at California ports, determining financial responsibility between importers and their licensed customs brokers becomes a critical legal question worth millions in potential liability. Under federal customs law at 19 USC 1484, the importer of record bears absolute liability for compliance failures, yet customs brokers can face regulatory sanctions under 19 CFR Part 111 and civil liability for breaches of reasonable care obligations. California importers processing billions in cargo through Los Angeles, Long Beach, Oakland, and San Diego must understand this liability framework before mistakes trigger penalties or liquidated damages. The broker-importer relationship involves complex duties of care, information exchange requirements, and allocation of compliance responsibilities. Recent CBP enforcement actions have simultaneously penalized both importers and brokers for the same violations. Our firm advises California importers on broker selection, service agreements, and liability allocation strategies.',
