  intro: 'When import transactions involve undetermined values at entry time—provisional pricing agreements, retroactive contract adjustments, or pending classification rulings—California importers face complex reconciliation requirements under 19 CFR § 141.113. The reconciliation entry process allows post-importation adjustments to duties, fees, and classifications without amending thousands of individual entries, but strict procedural requirements and deadlines transform administrative convenience into compliance risk for unprepared importers. California companies importing through Los Angeles, Long Beach, and Oakland must properly flag entries for reconciliation, file timely reconciliation entries within required timeframes, and maintain documentation supporting final value determinations. Missing reconciliation deadlines or failing to flag entries properly can result in permanent duty overpayments, lost refund opportunities, and liquidation of entries at incorrect values that cannot be corrected. Our firm advises California importers on reconciliation entry procedures, prepares reconciliation filings, and structures provisional pricing arrangements that comply with CBP requirements while providing operational flexibility.',
  services: 'Trembach Law Firm assists California importers with CBP reconciliation program enrollment and compliance including Type 09 entry procedures, eligible issues identification, reconciliation filing strategies, audit defense when CBP challenges entries, and liquidation extensions. Reconciliation entries allow California importers to import goods quickly using estimated data and perfect the entry later when final information becomes available, improving supply chain velocity while ensuring accuracy. Our attorneys help companies implement reconciliation programs strategically to optimize duty treatment while maintaining compliance. Contact us for reconciliation program enrollment assistance.',
  keywords: 'CBP reconciliation California, Type 09 entry, post-entry adjustment attorney, reconciliation refund claims, 19 CFR 141.113, customs value reconciliation lawyer, provisional pricing customs, reconciliation entry California, flagged entry procedures, ABI reconciliation filing, customs duty adjustment attorney, reconciliation protest lawyer California, retroactive price adjustments CBP, entry summary reconciliation, usmca attorney california',
