  id: 'cbp-focused-assessment-survival-guide-california',
  title: 'CBP Focused Assessment Survival Guide',
  subheading: 'What to Expect and How to Respond When CBP Comes Calling',
  intro: 'A Focused Assessment from U.S. Customs and Border Protection represents one of the most comprehensive compliance reviews an importer can face, systematically evaluating your entire import program through reasonable care standards. Unlike traditional audits examining specific transactions, a Focused Assessment evaluates your compliance infrastructure, internal controls, training programs, and risk management systems across a three-year period. For California importers handling high-volume Pacific trade routes through Los Angeles, Long Beach, and Oakland, understanding the FA process—from Pre-Assessment Survey through testing and final findings—can mean the difference between minimal disruption and significant penalties. The PAS phase determines audit scope, making early strategic intervention critical. Our firm guides California importers through every Focused Assessment phase, manages document production, controls audit scope, and negotiates favorable findings.',
  services: 'Trembach Law Firm has successfully guided California importers through over 150 CBP Focused Assessments, providing comprehensive audit defense from Pre-Assessment Survey through final report. We manage document production controlling narrative and limiting scope expansion, conduct parallel internal audits, prepare written policies and procedures demonstrating reasonable care, coordinate with foreign suppliers, respond to findings with corrective action plans, and negotiate risk ratings achieving Acceptable Risk determinations. Our FA survival methodology combines legal advocacy with practical compliance solutions protecting California importers from penalties. Contact us immediately upon receiving FA notification.',
