  id: 'korus-fta-qualification-california-importers',
  title: 'KORUS FTA Qualification California',
  subheading: 'Strategic Korea-US Trade Agreement Benefits for California Importers',
  intro: 'The Korea-United States Free Trade Agreement represents a cornerstone of trans-Pacific trade relations, offering California importers unprecedented duty-free access to Korean automotive components, electronics, chemicals, and consumer products. Under 19 CFR Part 10, Subpart R, qualifying goods enjoy immediate tariff elimination on over 95% of industrial and consumer products. California importers bringing Korean semiconductors, display panels, automotive parts, and machinery through Los Angeles and Oakland ports must navigate complex origin determination rules including change in tariff classification tests and regional value content thresholds. KORUS certification requires importers or exporters to prepare detailed origin declarations meeting specific data element requirements, maintain supporting documentation for five years, and respond to CBP verification requests. Failure to properly substantiate KORUS claims results in retroactive duty assessments. Our firm analyzes KORUS qualification, prepares certifications, and defends verification proceedings.',
  services: 'Trembach Law Firm assists California importers qualifying products for duty-free treatment under the Korea-United States Free Trade Agreement including rules of origin analysis, tariff shift determinations, regional value content calculations, certificates of origin preparation, and CBP verification defense. We analyze product-specific rules in KORUS Annex, perform RVC calculations, advise on accumulation and de minimis principles, prepare certificates with supporting documentation, respond to CBP verification requests, and litigate denied KORUS claims. California is the largest U.S. trading partner with Korea making KORUS qualification critical. Contact us for KORUS qualification analysis.',
