  id: 'fta-verification-defense-california',
  title: 'FTA Verification Defense California',
  subheading: 'Strategic Response to CBP Origin Verification Audits for California Importers',
  intro: 'California importers claiming preferential treatment under Free Trade Agreements face increasing scrutiny through CBP origin verification audits that challenge FTA duty-free claims through intensive documentation review. These comprehensive examinations conducted under 19 CFR Part 181 (USMCA), Part 178 (CAFTA-DR), and similar FTA implementing regulations require businesses to substantiate origin determinations through detailed cost breakdowns, manufacturing process documentation, and supplier declarations. With verification denial rates exceeding 40% for unprepared importers, California companies must implement robust verification defense strategies protecting millions in annual duty savings. CBP verifications take multiple forms including questionnaires, plant visits to foreign manufacturers, and requests for voluminous production records. The 30-day response deadline provides limited time to coordinate with foreign suppliers. Our firm manages FTA verification defense for California importers and presents evidence sustaining origin claims.',
  services: 'Trembach Law Firm represents California importers and exporters defending Free Trade Agreement verification proceedings initiated by CBP or foreign customs authorities including responses to CBP Form CF-28 requests, verification questionnaires demanding production records, foreign government verification visits to U.S. facilities, and litigation of denied FTA claims. We manage comprehensive verification responses coordinating with foreign suppliers, prepare production records and cost breakdowns proving origin compliance, host CBP verification visits, protect trade secrets during verification process, and litigate denied claims through protests and Court of International Trade appeals. Contact us immediately upon receiving verification request.',
