  title: 'Export Controls for Semiconductors',
  subheading: 'Navigating China Restrictions and Advanced Computing Chip Licensing Requirements',
  intro: 'The October 2022 and October 2023 semiconductor export control rules fundamentally transformed the regulatory landscape for California\'s semiconductor industry, imposing unprecedented restrictions on exports of advanced computing chips to China. These controls, codified primarily in 15 CFR 744.21 and through creation of new ECCNs 3A090 and 4A090, target advanced computing chips and semiconductor manufacturing equipment based on performance thresholds. California companies including NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel face complex licensing requirements affecting billions in revenue. The Foreign Direct Product Rule extensions at 15 CFR 734.9 expand U.S. jurisdiction globally, capturing foreign-produced items containing controlled U.S. technology. California semiconductor companies must evaluate product performance against total processing performance thresholds, understand Entity List restrictions, and navigate license requirements for China destinations. Our firm advises California semiconductor companies on advanced computing chip controls and prepares export license applications.',
  services: 'Trembach Law Firm provides specialized semiconductor export control counseling for California chip designers, manufacturers, and equipment suppliers navigating complex EAR controls on semiconductors, manufacturing equipment, and software under ECCNs 3A001, 3B001, 3C001, 3D001, and 3E001 including parameters-based controls on processing power, China-specific controls under new frameworks, deemed export risks in R&D environments, and foundry service controls. We classify semiconductors and equipment under technical parameters, advise on China export restrictions, prepare export license applications, implement deemed export controls in R&D facilities, and defend violations. Contact us for semiconductor-specific compliance.',
  keywords: 'semiconductor export controls, 15 CFR 744.21, ECCN 3A090, ECCN 4A090, China semiconductor restrictions, NVIDIA export controls, AMD licensing requirements, Intel export compliance, FDPR semiconductors, Entity List China, advanced computing chips, semiconductor manufacturing equipment, California export controls, October 2022 rules, October 2023 updates',
      publishedDate: '2025-11-07',
