  intro: 'The Uyghur Forced Labor Prevention Act has fundamentally transformed enforcement mechanisms for California apparel importers, particularly those operating within the Los Angeles Fashion District ecosystem handling billions in annual textile imports. Since June 21, 2022, the UFLPA\'s rebuttable presumption under 19 USC 1307 prohibits entry of goods wholly or partially produced in Xinjiang unless importers provide clear and convincing evidence demonstrating supply chain integrity. California apparel businesses importing cotton textiles, synthetic fabrics, polyester, and finished garments face unprecedented CBP scrutiny requiring sophisticated supply chain due diligence documentation. Detained shipments trigger immediate supply chain disruptions, requiring rapid response within tight CBP deadlines while gathering comprehensive evidence from foreign suppliers, conducting facility audits, and proving supply chain traceability. Our firm provides immediate detention response for California apparel importers, prepares UFLPA exception packages, and implements supply chain due diligence programs.',
